cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CR 

This paper deals with active integrity constraints in relational databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also uses ideas from algebraic fixpoint theory (cs.LO) to model database repairs as fixpoints of operators on databases. Additionally, the paper discusses algorithms for finding repairs, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of counter-intuitive examples in previous semantics, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
